Helmdeck depends on a number of third-party open-source libraries.
Their licenses are preserved in their respective Go module sources
under $GOPATH/pkg/mod and reproduced in any binary distribution per
their individual license terms. The most prominent dependencies and
their licenses:

  github.com/chromedp/chromedp                    MIT
  github.com/chromedp/cdproto                     MIT
  github.com/docker/docker                        Apache-2.0
  github.com/google/uuid                          BSD-3-Clause
  github.com/minio/minio-go/v7                    Apache-2.0
  github.com/gobwas/ws                            MIT
  modernc.org/sqlite                              BSD-3-Clause
  go.opentelemetry.io/otel                        Apache-2.0
  github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5                    MIT

The browser sidecar image bundles unmodified copies of:

  Chromium                LGPL-2.1+ (and others; see /usr/share/doc/chromium)
  Marp CLI                MIT
  Tesseract OCR           Apache-2.0
  Xvfb / XFCE4 / noVNC    MIT / GPL / GPL combinations
  ffmpeg                  LGPL-2.1+ (default build)
  scrot, xdotool          BSD/MIT

The Garage object store bundled in the Compose stack is licensed
AGPLv3 by the Deuxfleurs collective. It is invoked as a separate
process over the S3 HTTP API and is not statically linked into
the helmdeck control plane; the AGPL boundary is the network
interface between the two processes.
